I'm trying to build a resilient service where one component fails and I want the whole system not to crash. I have some code using `Result` but it feels fragile when things go wrong. Here is what I have so far: 

fn handle_request() -> Result<String, Error> {
    let data = fetch_from_external_api()?;
    if let Err(e) = validate_data(&data) {
        return Err(e);
    }
    Ok(data.to_string())
}

I keep getting panic when the external API is slow or unavailable. I need to fall back to a simpler behavior instead of failing completely.
